===Etymology 1===
The crooked sense may at least partly derive from the same source as the "cater" in {{m|en|cater-corner}}, which some would derive from {{cog|frm|catre||four}}- in reference to four corners/square- from {{cog|fro|quatre||four}}, from {{cog|la|quattuor}}. This is disputed by others, who suggest a possible {{etyl|non|-}} or other Scandinavian origin. See {{m|en|cater-corner}} and {{m|en|cater-corner}} for more.

See ''[[wampish]]'' (def. 2)

